feat(display-tablets): add photo gallery screens with S3 storage

Implement complete photo gallery feature for display tablets allowing
caregivers to upload and manage family photos organized in custom screens.

## Database Layer
- Add migration 018 with photo_screens and photos tables
- Support max 5 screens per tablet, 6 photos per screen
- Cascade deletes and proper indexing

## Domain Layer
- New entities: PhotoScreen, Photo, PhotoScreenWithPhotos
- New types: DisplayMode, SlideshowTransition, SlideshowOrder
- New errors: PhotoScreenNotFoundError, PhotoNotFoundError,
  MaxPhotoScreensReachedError, MaxPhotosReachedError,
  UnsupportedFileFormatError, FileTooLargeError
- S3 configuration added to env.ts

## Repository Layer
- 13 new methods in HouseholdRepository interface
- Full PostgreSQL implementation
- InMemoryRepository stubs for test compatibility

## Storage Service
- S3StorageService with upload/delete operations
- Image compression using Sharp library
- CloudFront URL generation
- Format and size validation (JPEG/PNG/WebP, 5MB max)

## Use Cases (9 total)
Photo Screens: Create, Update, Delete, List, Get
Photos: Upload, Update, Delete, Reorder

## API Routes (9 endpoints)
- POST /photo-screens - Create screen
- GET /photo-screens - List screens  
- GET /photo-screens/:screenId - Get screen details
- PUT /photo-screens/:screenId - Update screen
- DELETE /photo-screens/:screenId - Delete screen
- POST /photo-screens/:screenId/photos - Upload photo
- PUT /photos/:photoId - Update photo metadata
- DELETE /photos/:photoId - Delete photo
- PUT /photos/reorder - Reorder photos

## Validation & Security
- Zod schemas for all endpoints
- Permission checks (caregivers only)
- Real MIME type validation
- File size limits with automatic compression
- Household isolation enforced
- TypeScript exactOptionalPropertyTypes compliance

## Dependencies
- @aws-sdk/client-s3 - AWS S3 client
- @fastify/multipart - File upload handling
- sharp - Image processing and compression

The feature is production-ready and follows all project architecture
guidelines (strict layering, strong typing, explicit validation,
centralized error handling).
